  codeText: "<color=#E7755B>let</color> <color=#5bcde7>x</color> =0;\r\n<color=#E7755B>loop</color>(10)\n{\n   
    <color=#E7755B>let</color> <color=#5bcde7>x</color> =<color=#5bcde7>x</color>+1;\r\n   
    <color=#5bcde7>out</color>(<color=#5bcde7>x</color>);\r\n}\n\n<color=#E7755B>let</color>
    <color=#5bcde7>x</color> = 0;\n<color=#E7755B>loop</color>(<color=#5bcde7>x</color><10)\n{\n   
    <color=#E7755B>let</color> <color=#5bcde7>x</color> = <color=#5bcde7>x</color>
    + 1;\n    <color=#5bcde7>out</color>(<color=#5bcde7>x</color>);\n}"
  descriptionText: 'Loops are used for executing a block of code a number of times.


    Loop
    can be used in 2 ways :


    loop(Integer)

    {

    Loops until the Integer
    is 0

    Integer decrements automatically every loop

    }



    -----------------



    loop(Boolean)

    {

    Loops
    until xBool is false

    }'
  code: 'let x = 0;

    loop(10)

    {

    let x = x +1;

    out(x);

    }


    let
    x = 0;

    loop(x < 10)

    {

    let x = x + 1;

    out(x);

    }'
